  "notes": [
    "Pinned OCI SDK contract: CreateConfig, GetConfig, ListConfigs, UpdateConfig, and DeleteConfig all require the query apmDomainId, address one polymorphic Config root, and use polymorphic CreateConfigDetails, UpdateConfigDetails, and ConfigSummary shapes across AGENT, OPTIONS, MACS_APM_EXTENSION, METRIC_GROUP, APDEX, and SPAN_FILTER.",
    "ListConfigs exposes configType, displayName, and optionsGroup query filters, but the reviewed runtime still owns subtype dispatch, bind-versus-create policy, and mutation parity over the published union Config surface.",
    "Repo-authored reuse is explicit: the runtime mirrors apmDomainId into status, skips pre-create lookup until the selected subtype exposes enough identity, and only adopts a unique exact match on configType, displayName, group, filterId, filterText, namespace, managementAgentId, matchAgentsWithAttributeValue, and serviceName."
  ]
